## Overview
Discovered a Stored XSS vulnerability where user input is stored and rendered without sanitization.

## Steps
1. Located comment input field
2. Injected payload:
   <script>alert(1)</script>
3. Submitted comment
4. Observed execution on page load
5. Refreshed page → payload executed again

## Key Insight
The application stores user input and renders it directly into HTML without encoding.

## Impact
- Persistent execution
- Affects all users viewing the page
- Potential for session hijacking and admin compromise
